Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
f00a47d9-f4fe-4b46-9d56-ae1820b1f733.359cadc9-6146-401a-8b78-5828c78d8034.prompt=Enter a value for sublist f00a47d9-f4fe-4b46-9d56-ae1820b1f733.4e07d63f-6f65-4fa0-85c8-c57d3f3ceeb9.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

If the matchType is RegEx, input matchTo is the regular expression like \: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. Input toMatch is the actual string to check to see if it matches the matchTo expression.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against. 
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.

f00a47d9-f4fe-4b46-9d56-ae1820b1f733.7c6b3786-7c16-4035-8a63-2f6789a0ddbb.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists. Default is a comma
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.

f00a47d9-f4fe-4b46-9d56-ae1820b1f733.description=
This workflow maps the CSA service component type to the uCMDB CI type based on the Cloud Service Automation query

Inputs\:

svcComponentId	- CSA Service Component Id of the component to find uCMDB CI type mapping for
svcComponentType	- CSA Component type of the component to find uCMDB CI type mapping for
userIdentifier	- CSA User Identifier 

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
